  "body": "### Description\nThis test ensures that when all nodes are stopped, that the final clique validator cannot create another block.\n\nHowever, the way its written can potentially be flakey depending timing.\n\nThe crux of the test:\n\n* Start 3 nodes (Required to create a 3-node genesis file)\n* Stop nodes 2 & 3\n* Ensure no blocks are created <-- This can fail.\n\nThe final step _can_ fail, as its _possible_ that the prior to block was _not_ created by Node-1, and thus, it is allowed to create another block, breaking the assertion.\n\nHow do we fix it?\nPrior to doing the assertion, wait for the headblock to be proposed by Node-1 (potentially time-zero), THEN ensure no further blocks are created.",
